  <h2>5. Social Media Platform Integrations (Including TikTok)</h2>
  <p>
    Our Services let you connect your social media accounts — including TikTok —
    so we can publish and schedule content to those accounts on your behalf. When
    you connect a TikTok account, you authorize us through TikTok's official login
    and consent flow, and we (together with our authorized API provider) access
    and store only what is needed to provide the Service:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Basic account information</strong> returned by TikTok, such as the
    account's open ID, display name, and avatar, used to identify the connected
    account.</li>
    <li><strong>Secure access and refresh tokens</strong> issued by TikTok, used
    solely to publish or schedule the content you approve. These are stored
    securely and are never sold or used for advertising.</li>
    <li><strong>The videos, images, captions, and post settings</strong> you
    choose to publish through the Service.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We use this access only to publish or schedule content that you or your
    authorized team members have approved. Our access to, use of, and transfer of
    information received from the TikTok APIs adhere to the TikTok Developer Terms
    of Service and the TikTok Developer Data Sharing Agreement. You can revoke our
    access at any time from your TikTok account settings (Security &amp;
    permissions → Manage app permissions) or by emailing
    <a href="mailto:hello@synchrosocial.com">hello@synchrosocial.com</a>, after
    which we stop accessing the account and delete the associated tokens.
  </p>

